<s> Can a root node which is not a document node be a parent node?  </s>
<s> The last sentence in 4 implies that a fragment has a "root node" which is not a document node.  </s>
<s> Can such a "root node" have child nodes or, more precisely, be a parent node?  </s>
<s> Andrew Watt  </s>
<s> Yes, it can.  </s>
<s> The XQuery expression yields an element node a which has no parent (and is therefore a root), and which has a child b.  </s>
<s> Since the latest XSLT 2.0 draft it is also possible to create such structures in XSLT: Michael Kay  </s>
